{"title_page": "Noble Savage (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Noble Savage\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Marco Carmel]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Marco Carmel\n| starring       = [[Alon Aboutboul]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|df=yes|2018|6||Cinema South Film Festival|ref1=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/israel/jerusalem-post/20180603/281831464418087|title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News|website=www.pressreader.com|accessdate=15 September 2018}}</ref>|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 94 minutes\n| country        = Israel\n| language       = Hebrew\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Noble Savage''''' ({{lang-he|\u05e4\u05e8\u05d0 \u05d0\u05e6\u05d9\u05dc}}) is a 2018 Israeli [[drama film]] directed by [[Marco Carmel]].<ref name=\"IFF\">{{cite web |url=http://intl.filmfund.org.il/films/?id=&nom=002815&film=Noble%20Savage |title=Noble Savage |work=Israel Film Fund |accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"JC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.jer-cin.org.il/en/event/23786 |title=Noble Savage |work= Jerusalem Cinematheque |accessdate=4 August 2018}}</ref> In July 2018, it was one of five films nominated for the [[Ophir Award]] for Best Picture.<ref name=\"Ophir\">{{cite web |url=http://thefilmexperience.net/blog/2018/6/26/what-will-israel-submit-to-the-oscars.html |title=What will Israel submit to the Oscars? |work=The Film Experience |date=26 June 2018 |accessdate=26 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Alon Aboutboul]] as Yom Tov\n* [[Moris Cohen]] as Nahshon\n* [[Liat Ekta]] as Sima\n* [[Shira Haas]] as Anna\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8665606|Noble Savage}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Noble Savage}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2018 drama films]]\n[[Category:Israeli films]]\n[[Category:Israeli drama films]]\n[[Category:Hebrew-language films]]\n{{Israel-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Noble Savage\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Marco Carmel]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Marco Carmel\n| starring       = [[Alon Aboutboul]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2018|6||Cinema South Film Festival|ref1=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/israel/jerusalem-post/20180603/281831464418087|title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News|website=www.pressreader.com|accessdate=15 September 2018}}</ref>|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 94 minutes\n| country        = Israel\n| language       = Hebrew\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Noble Savage''''' ({{lang-he|\u05e4\u05e8\u05d0 \u05d0\u05e6\u05d9\u05dc}}) is a 2018 Israeli [[drama film]] directed by [[Marco Carmel]].<ref name=\"IFF\">{{cite web |url=http://intl.filmfund.org.il/films/?id=&nom=002815&film=Noble%20Savage |title=Noble Savage |work=Israel Film Fund |accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"JC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.jer-cin.org.il/en/event/23786 |title=Noble Savage |work= Jerusalem Cinematheque |accessdate=4 August 2018}}</ref> In July 2018, it was one of five films nominated for the [[Ophir Award]] for Best Picture.<ref name=\"Ophir\">{{cite web |url=http://thefilmexperience.net/blog/2018/6/26/what-will-israel-submit-to-the-oscars.html |title=What will Israel submit to the Oscars? |work=The Film Experience |date=26 June 2018 |accessdate=26 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Alon Aboutboul]] as Yom Tov\n* [[Moris Cohen]] as Nahshon\n* [[Liat Ekta]] as Sima\n* [[Shira Haas]] as Anna\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8665606|Noble Savage}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Noble Savage}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[