ks magistrates and judges to consider alternatives to incarceration.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.richmond.com/news/virginia/update-virginia-officials-asking-law-enforcement-to-avoid-arrests-when/article_67dbe141-da92-504b-b74d-e7c9ed8a118c.html|title=UPDATE: Virginia officials asking law enforcement to avoid arrests when possible|last=reports|first=From staff|website=Richmond Times-Dispatch|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320061816/https://www.richmond.com/news/virginia/update-virginia-officials-asking-law-enforcement-to-avoid-arrests-when/article_67dbe141-da92-504b-b74d-e7c9ed8a118c.html|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Virginia reports 24 new COVID-19 cases, bringing the total to 101.\n\n====March 20====\nAs of March 20, the U.S had 19,285 confirmed cases of COVID-19 resulting in 249 deaths.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-updates-us-deaths-cases-stay-home-order-trump/2880695001/|title=Coronavirus updates: U.S. infections approach 20,000; NY, Illinois unleash strict rules; 150 Detroit cops quarantined|first1=Ryan|last1=Miller|first2=Marco|last2=Cava|date=March 20, 2020|website=usatoday.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321020308/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-updates-us-deaths-cases-stay-home-order-trump/2880695001/|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*California: Los Angeles Mayor [[Eric Garcetti]] promised that no one will go to jail for violating the [[stay-at-home order]] that goes into effect at midnight. However, a major purpose of the order is to provide enforcement for businesses which are not complying.<ref>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ L.A. Mayor Promises 'People Aren't Going To Be Marched Into Jail' Under New Safer At Home Order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320200928/https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Dominic Patten, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> Marijuana dispensaries are classified \"essential\".<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html Marijuana dispensaries are deemed 'essential' in LA, allowed to stay open during coronavirus order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321025617/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html |date=March 21, 2020 }} By Allen Kim, CNN, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Illinois: Governor [[J.B. Pritzker]] issued a stay-at-home order. The order will become effective March 21 and will remain in place until April 7 but could go longer.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/coronavirus-illinois-issue-stay-home-order-13-million-residents-california-n1164901?fbclid=IwAR0hnei6UFmSAf_aiG9deV6sjuK8LQqcB9T1s8mpqSQHe7WR3ILy0pluCZU Coronavirus: Illinois issues stay-at-home order for 13 million residents] By Minyvonne Burke, NBC News, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*New York: Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] issued a state-wide order that all non-essential workers must stay at home. He noted that the number of coronavirus cases in the state had gone from zero on March 4 to over 2,900.<ref name=deadline>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ New York Governor Issues Statewide Stay-At-Home Order For All Non-Essential Workers] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320170143/https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Erik Pederson, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> The same day, Coronavirus cases in New York exceed 7000.<ref name=CNN>\"[https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320204137/https://www.cnn.com/202