The state has 88 confirmed cases across 19 counties. 26 cases involved hospitalization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|title=88 confirmed cases of coronavirus in Ohio; 26 hospitalized|date=March 18, 2020|website=10tv.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318055740/https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Governor Mike DeWine announces 181 Divisions of Motor Vehicle locations will close until further notice. Five will stay open to process commercial driver license applications and renewals. DeWine asks state legislatures to allow a grace period for people whose licenses have expired. Barbershops, salons, and tattoo parlors are closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-from-governor-odh-set-for-for-2-p-m/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Wednesday update: 88 cases of COVID-19 confirmed|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211617/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-from-governor-odh-set-for-for-2-p-m/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Businesses that do stay open are asked to take their employees' temperatures every day before allowing them entry to work and to send sick employees home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/dewine-businesses-should-take-employees-temperatures-every-day/|title=DeWine: Businesses should take temperatures of employees every day|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211624/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/dewine-businesses-should-take-employees-temperatures-every-day/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Mayor Andrew Ginther declares a state of emergency in [[Columbus, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/mayor-ginther-declares-state-of-emergency-in-columbus/|title=Coronavirus in Columbus: Mayor Ginther declares State of Emergency, confirms 2 new cases in city|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211620/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/mayor-ginther-declares-state-of-emergency-in-columbus/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Oregon: Oregon Governor Kat Brown issues executive order extending the closure of K-12 public schools until April 28.<ref name=\"auto2\"/>  \n*Pennsylvania: The state announces its first death in [[Northampton County, Pennsylvania|Northampton County]] following the addition of 37 new cases bringing the total to 133 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mcall.com/coronavirus/mc-nws-coronavirus-death-norco-20200318-ndbg5g56l5g7rmzukwx67yzmgu-story.html|title=First Pennsylvania coronavirus death reported -- from Northampton County|author=Morning Call Staff|website=mcall.com|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211932/https://www.mcall.com/coronavirus/mc-nws-coronavirus-death-norco-20200318-ndbg5g56l5g7rmzukwx67yzmgu-story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pennlive.com/news/2020/03/pa-confirms-37-new-coronavirus-cases-statewide-total-rises-to-133.html|title=Pa. confirms 37 new coronavirus cases as statewide total rises to 133|date=2020-03-18|website=pennlive|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211933/https://www.pennlive.com/news/2020/03/pa-confirms-37-new-coronavirus-cases-statewide-total-rises-to-133.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*South Carolina: The state confirms more cases of the COVID-19, totaling at 60 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wistv.com/2020/03/18/coronavirus-cases-sc-continue-rise-cases-reported-counties/|title=Coronavirus cases in S.C. continue to rise: 60 cases reported in 14 counties|last=Mallory|first=Laurel|website=wistv.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319015547/https://www.wistv.com/2020/03/18/coronavirus-cases-sc-continue-rise-cases-reported-counties/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Utah: U.S. congressman [[Ben McAdams]] tests positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/utah-congressman-ben-mcadams-says-he-tested-positive-for-covid/article_b9b040dc-9d52-5fb0-853d-afa6040f9987.html|title=Utah Congressman Ben McAdams says he tested positive for COVID-19|last=Herald|first=Connor Richards Daily|website=Daily Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319083543/https://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/utah-congressman-ben-mcadams-says-he-tested-positive-for-covid/article_b9b040dc-9d52-5fb0-853d-afa6040f9987.html|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====March 19====\n3,000 doctors and medical workers sign a letter asking [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement|ICE]] to release individuals and families detained for immigration violations, noting the harsh, overcrowded conditions are ripe for the propagation of the coronavirus.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-us-doctors-demand-immediate-093956554.html Coronavirus: US doctors demand immediate release of prisoners and detainees to avert disaster] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195214/https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-us-doctors-demand-immediate-093956554.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Andrew Naughtie, The Independent, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n* California: The state has ordered the closure of all museums, malls and other all non-essential workplaces effective Marc